Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @Carrot{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the carrots on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Peel the @Garlic Cloves{3}.

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes.

Add the potatoes and whole garlic cloves to the water and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While the potatoes cook, pour the @Water{225%ml} for the jus into a small saucepan, bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @Red Wine Jus Paste{22%g}, then reduce the heat to medium-high.

> If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with salt and pepper.

> Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{5%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of minutes.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

When the carrots have ~{5%minutes} left, drizzle over the @Honey{15%g}. Turn to coat. Return to the oven for the remaining time.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once the potatoes and garlic are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add the cheese, a splash of @?milk{} and @Butter{20%g} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once rested, slice your steaks and share between your #plates{}.

Serve the cheesy garlic mash and roasted carrots on the side.

Pour over the red wine jus to finish.

Enjoy!